      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "If we divide the God Object into smaller classes, then it's the task of Client to\norganize what parameters to brings and how to orchestrate those classes.\nThis is why we used to create Orchestration class called Facade.\n\nOrchestration service is not a God-Object, rather it acts as Single-point-of-\nEntry for our application. It doesn't perform operations on its own, rather\ndelegates it forward.\n\nLike in Microservices API, we have Controller which defines the API endpoints\nand acts as single-entry point.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "If we divide the God Object into smaller classes, then it's the task of Client to organize what parameters to brings and how to orchestrate those classes.\nThis is why we used to create Orchestration class called Facade.\n\nOrchestration service is not a God-Object, rather it acts as Single-point-of-Entry for our application. It doesn't perform operations on its own, rather delegates it forward.\n\nLike in Microservices API, we have Controller which defines the API endpoints and acts as single-entry point.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
