      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782027396196,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "7. Overuse of Getters/Setters:",
      "fontSize": 26.8,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "7. Overuse of Getters/Setters:",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "qts-1hc2QMJeX-ezSbi-Y",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 67.36244712928081,
      "y": 4247.449154411241,
      "width": 863.6778762817383,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "cross-hatch",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 70,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1F",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 44367790,
      "version": 2234,
      "versionNonce": 1246365042,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782027396196,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It may sound counter-intuitive at first since we require getter()/setter() for accessing\nor setting private Attributes.\nBut we also need to realize those attributes were private, bcuz we didn't wanted it to\nbe accessible from outside at first place. \n\nWe should be conciously thinking which Attributes need getter() or setter() or both;\nbut instead we mostly generate getter() & setter() for all private fields before-hand\nwhich is a wrong approach.\nAlso most IDEs suggest to generate all Getter/Setter which has made it worse.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It may sound counter-intuitive at first since we require getter()/setter() for accessing or setting private Attributes.\nBut we also need to realize those attributes were private, bcuz we didn't wanted it to be accessible from outside at first place. \n\nWe should be conciously thinking which Attributes need getter() or setter() or both; but instead we mostly generate getter() & setter() for all private fields before-hand which is a wrong approach.\nAlso most IDEs suggest to generate all Getter/Setter which has made it worse.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "1Zdt5u4Dygnej1q-87tFY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 60.116623436325796,
      "y": 4594.678586118689,
      "width": 346.4969787597656,
      "height": 33.5,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 80,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1G",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1859022638,
      "version": 1871,
      "versionNonce": 835454446,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782027412257,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "8. Premature Optimization:",
      "fontSize": 26.8,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "8. Premature Optimization:",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "_NP6IPdG3cso3PBVAse4U",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 59.829163336539494,
      "y": 4644.094066371952,
      "width": 863.6778762817383,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "cross-hatch",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 70,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2111068526,
      "version": 2460,
      "versionNonce": 648844590,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782027481602,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "It states that before optimizing for performance, we should 1st focus on making it\nwork. There's also a popular quote:",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "It states that before optimizing for performance, we should 1st focus on making it work. There's also a popular quote:",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "YRoZMYElWue4wkbSQbseL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 222.08036279395822,
      "y": 4699.162641025682,
      "width": 293.4595947265625,
      "height": 27,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#846358",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "cross-hatch",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 80,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1I",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 116583794,
      "version": 99,
      "versionNonce": 805141806,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782027558938,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"Make it work, then make it fast\"",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"Make it work, then make it fast\"",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "RBAZN1LFdHq8pPImy5AZz",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 58.03731127624863,
      "y": 4753.327504163959,
      "width": 863.6778762817383,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
      "fillStyle": "cross-hatch",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 70,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 890993390,
      "version": 2777,
      "versionNonce": 1968807854,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782027644306,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "First priority should be making our application to do the intended behaviour before\noptimizing it.\nLike even in DSA for any problem, we 1st think about Brute-Force approach and then\nonly comes to Optimized/Memoized solution.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "First priority should be making our application to do the intended behaviour before optimizing it.\nLike even in DSA for any problem, we 1st think about Brute-Force approach and then only comes to Optimized/Memoized solution.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "I7jKYRgRfqZsx2MftkoPZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 56.770582067196216,
      "y": 4994.764519966188,
      "width": 300.58856201171875,
      "height": 33.5,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 80,
      "groupIds": [],
